oc:kn_0f0dd904 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When documenting any SOX control test" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Every control test workpaper must include: control identification (ID, description, type, frequency, risk/assertion), test design (objective, procedures, expected evidence, sample rationale), test execution (population, sample details, pass/fail results, exceptions), conclusion (assessment, basis, impact, compensating controls), and sign-off (tester and reviewer with dates)." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Complete documentation ensures defensibility of audit conclusions and satisfies external auditor and regulatory requirements." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_15551b1c a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When evaluating or documenting audit evidence" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Verbal confirmations alone are insufficient evidence. Undated documents, evidence without identifiable performer/approver, and generic system reports without timestamps are also insufficient." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Audit evidence must be independently verifiable, traceable, and timestamped to meet SOX documentation standards." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_1e40dfd6 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When testing automated controls" ;
    oc:directiveContent "For automated controls, if the system configuration has not changed, one test is typically sufficient for the period. Supplement with ITGC change management testing to confirm no unauthorized changes occurred." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Automated controls operate consistently once configured; the primary risk is unauthorized or untested changes to the configuration." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_4cda9f34 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When a control deficiency is identified" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Deficiency remediation: 1. Root cause analysis (design gap, execution failure, staffing, training, system issue) 2. Define remediation plan (redesign, training, system enhancement, added review) 3. Set target completion date 4. Assign remediation owner 5. Plan re-testing validation of the remediated control" ;
    oc:stepOrder 2 .

oc:kn_6487c32f a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:OutputFormat ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When organizing SOX testing documentation" ;
    oc:directiveContent """SOX Testing/
├── [Year]/
│   ├── Scoping and Risk Assessment/
│   ├── Revenue Cycle/
│   │   ├── Control Matrix
│   │   ├── Walkthrough Documentation
│   │   ├── Test Workpapers (one per control)
│   │   └── Supporting Evidence
│   ├── Procure to Pay/
│   ├── Financial Close/
│   ├── IT General Controls/
│   ├── Entity Level Controls/
│   └── Summary and Conclusions/
│       ├── Deficiency Evaluation
│       └── Management Assessment""" ;
    oc:templateVariables "Control Cycle",
        "Year" .

oc:kn_6506cf80 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When selecting audit samples" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use random selection for large transaction-level populations, targeted selection for risk-based testing or small/varied populations, systematic selection for sequential populations needing even coverage, and haphazard selection only when random is impractical and population is homogeneous." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Matching the sample selection method to the population characteristics maximizes both statistical validity and testing efficiency." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_6c2e0b53 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Always, when using this skill" ;
    oc:directiveContent "This skill does not provide audit or legal advice. All testing workpapers and assessments must be reviewed by qualified financial professionals." ;
    oc:hasRationale "SOX compliance involves legal and regulatory obligations that require professional judgment and accountability beyond what an AI assistant can provide." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_b156af6c a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:KnownIssue ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When evaluating entity-level controls" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Ineffective entity-level controls, especially audit committee oversight and tone at the top, are strong indicators of a material weakness regardless of process-level control effectiveness." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Entity-level controls set the foundation for the entire control environment; their failure undermines process-level controls across the board." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_b5d457fc a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When conducting a full SOX 404 assessment cycle" ;
    oc:directiveContent "SOX 404 testing lifecycle: 1. Scope significant accounts and relevant assertions 2. Assess risk of material misstatement per account 3. Identify and document controls addressing each risk 4. Test design effectiveness (walkthroughs) and operating effectiveness (inspection, observation, re-performance, inquiry) 5. Evaluate deficiencies and classify severity 6. Report assessment and any material weaknesses" ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

oc:kn_c4e6bf19 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When testing IT-dependent manual controls" ;
    oc:directiveContent "For IT-dependent manual controls, test both the manual control (review, approval, follow-up) AND the completeness and accuracy of the underlying system-generated report/data (IPE testing)." ;
    oc:hasRationale "A manual review is only as reliable as the data it relies on; IPE testing ensures the system-generated information is trustworthy." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_e0511c54 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When evaluating control deficiencies" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Do not classify a deficiency in isolation. Always evaluate whether individually minor deficiencies in the same process or affecting the same assertion combine to form a significant deficiency or material weakness." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Deficiency aggregation is required under SOX guidance; individually minor deficiencies can together represent a material risk." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

